Class EPGCS

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible, javax.swing.RootPaneContainer, javax.swing.WindowConstants

    public class EPGCS
extends javax.swing.JFrame
    Main class for creating material data and displaying the cross sections for electrons, positrons and photons. EPGCS stands for Electron, Positron and Gamma Cross Sections.
    Medium can be autoselected from density file; Medium can also be user defined but avoiding duplicates, in other words only mixtures can be manually created. PEGS4 can handle compound case (see SPINIT subroutine), i.e. H2 liquid with ne=2 and z[0]=z[1]=1.0, but this is not allowed here (by design, we want elements and their fraction by weight, so we can't have H and H with non sense fractions).
    Author:
    Dan Fulea, 22 AUG. 2005
